rComments: Mediocre prof, really wants studends to do well. after a low average on 1st midterm he made the 2nd midterm so easy that class avg went up 15%. final was the exact same as the 2nd midter with a few questions from newer chapters. You can learn this whole class from the textbook, dont bother coming to class, easy course though.

This professor is very sub-standard in his teaching ability, preparedness, and clarity. His slides are full of typos and he is not familiar with their contents nor the relevance of tables/charts. He only asks questions that are too basic to bother answering but never ones that provoke thought or discussion. Avoid at all costs. Total joke.

Knows absolutely nothing about the subject matter, and reads straight from the slides the textbook gives to you. He often does not know any answers to questions students ask. Took the class as a summer course, midterms were extremely easy. I have no idea why someone thought this guy would make a good prof. Horrible horrible class.

Basically expects students to learn from the textbook by rote memorization. Just regurgitates from the textbook in class and expects you to give back lists as they appear in the book for the exams. Interesting subject, but he killed it. No context is given for the information. If you have a photographic memory, you may do well in his class.

Spends much time arguing semantics with students and is often unable to explain himself to students. Difficult marker. Rather than trying a different approach, he will continue to repeat himself to a confused student

He is not very clear in his explanations. Since there are no pre-requisites to the course, there was a lot of time wasted on explaining concepts understood by those who took intro to macro/microeconomics (ex. nearly 2 lectures on PPP). The exams were very difficult and were the only thing used for grading.

This class covers alot of material and tests are very hard. Memorization of long lists with plenty of details is required. Professor is passionate about economics, and is helpful. The slides are from the textbook, but thats how the course was desgined.
I don't pay 5 grand a year to be read to from a textbook, his classes are horrible
You need to know the material inside out for the test and they are really hard.  A lot of material in the course.
